{"parentUuid":"13feb7fc-0170-4a83-94aa-08b487d85882","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"e7b0d134-3f2c-4a56-aabb-41cd6db44a23","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GqzG1xGTEmkZXH246iu91e","type":"tool_result","content":"400\t    fi\n401\t    state_save \"$sid\" \"$new_state\"\n402\t    ;;\n403\t  *)\n404\t    echo \"Phase 1 prototype — only freeze/unfreeze supported.\"\n405\t    exit 1\n406\t    ;;\n407\tesac\n408\t```\n409\t\n410\tMake executable: `chmod +x scripts/smart-rename-cli.sh`\n411\t\n412\t- [ ] **Step 2: Write minimal `skills/smart-rename/SKILL.md` (Phase 1)**\n413\t\n414\t```markdown\n415\t---\n416\tname: smart-rename\n417\tdescription: Manage the smart-session-rename plugin. Phase 1 prototype supports freeze/unfreeze only.\n418\t---\n419\t\n420\t# /smart-rename (Phase 1 prototype)\n421\t\n422\tWhen the user invokes `/smart-rename freeze` or `/smart-rename unfreeze`, run the matching command via the Bash tool and report the output.\n423\t\n424\t## Determining session id\n425\t\n426\tIf `$CLAUDE_SESSION_ID` is set, the script uses it. Otherwise it derives the id from the transcript filename.\n427\t\n428\t## Commands\n429\t\n430\t### `/smart-rename freeze`\n431\t\n432\t```bash\n433\t${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/smart-rename-cli.sh freeze \"$CLAUDE_TRANSCRIPT_PATH\"\n434\t```\n435\t\n436\t### `/smart-rename unfreeze`\n437\t\n438\t```bash\n439\t${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/smart-rename-cli.sh unfreeze \"$CLAUDE_TRANSCRIPT_PATH\"\n440\t```\n441\t\n442\tAny other subcommand: reply \"Not yet implemented (Phase 1 prototype).\"\n443\t```\n444\t\n445\t- [ ] **Step 3: Manual smoke test**\n446\t\n447\tLaunch an interactive Claude Code session (dev install of this plugin). Run:\n448\t\n449\t```\n450\t/smart-rename freeze\n451\t```\n452\t\n453\tExpected: \"Smart rename: FROZEN for session `<id>`\". Verify state:\n454\t\n455\t```bash\n456\tcat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/<id>.json\" | jq .\n457\t```\n458\tShould show `\"frozen\": true`.\n459\t\n460\tThen `/smart-rename unfreeze` — verify state shows `\"frozen\": false`.\n461\t\n462\t- [ ] **Step 4: Document results in `docs/test-results/2026-04-14-skill-prototype.md`**\n463\t\n464\tRecord:\n465\t- Was `$CLAUDE_SESSION_ID` available in the skill environment?\n466\t- Did Bash tool execute the script from `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}`?\n467\t- Any race with the Stop hook firing after the skill's own turn?\n468\t- Did session-id derivation from `$CLAUDE_TRANSCRIPT_PATH` work?\n469\t\n470\t**If the prototype succeeded:** proceed to Phase 2.\n471\t**If it failed:** stop here and adjust the mechanism (e.g., pass session_id explicitly, different invocation pattern) before continuing.\n472\t\n473\t- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n474\t\n475\t```bash\n476\tgit add scripts/smart-rename-cli.sh skills/smart-rename/SKILL.md docs/test-results/2026-04-14-skill-prototype.md\n477\tgit commit -m \"feat(v1.5): Phase 1 skill prototype (freeze/unfreeze) validates mechanism\"\n478\t```\n479\t\n480\t---\n481\t\n482\t## Phase 2: Config and logger, refactor state\n483\t\n484\t### Task 2.1: Create `lib/config.sh` with tests\n485\t\n486\t**Files:**\n487\t- Create: `scripts/lib/config.sh`\n488\t- Create: `tests/unit/test-config.sh`\n489\t- Modify: `config/default-config.json`\n490\t\n491\t- [ ] **Step 1: Replace `config/default-config.json`**\n492\t\n493\t```json\n494\t{\n495\t  \"enabled\": true,\n496\t  \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n497\t\n498\t  \"max_budget_calls\": 6,\n499\t  \"overflow_manual_slots\": 2,\n500\t  \"first_call_work_threshold\": 20,\n501\t  \"ongoing_work_threshold\": 40,\n502\t\n503\t  \"reattach_interval\": 10,\n504\t  \"circuit_breaker_threshold\": 3,\n505\t  \"lock_stale_seconds\": 60,\n506\t  \"llm_timeout_seconds\": 25,\n507\t\n508\t  \"log_level\": \"info\",\n509\t  \"max_clauses\": 5,\n510\t  \"max_domain_chars\": 30,\n511\t  \"max_user_msg_chars\": 500,\n512\t  \"max_assistant_chars\": 500\n513\t}\n514\t```\n515\t\n516\tNote: `lock_stale_seconds` is 60 (was 30) to provide 2× safety margin over `llm_timeout_seconds: 25`.\n517\t\n518\t- [ ] **Step 2: Create `tests/unit/test-config.sh`**\n519\t\n520\t```bash\n521\t#!/usr/bin/env bash\n522\tset -euo pipefail\n523\t\n524\tSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\n525\tsource \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../../scripts/lib/config.sh\"\n526\t\n527\tPASS=0; FAIL=0\n528\tassert_eq() { local d=\"$1\" e=\"$2\" a=\"$3\"; [[ \"$e\" == \"$a\" ]] && { echo \"  ✓ $d\"; ((PASS++)) || true; } || { echo \"  ✗ $d: '$e' vs '$a'\"; ((FAIL++)) || true; }; }\n529\t\n530\techo \"=== config.sh tests ===\"\n531\texport CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA=\"$(mktemp -d)\"\n532\tfor v in SMART_RENAME_ENABLED SMART_RENAME_MODEL SMART_RENAME_BUDGET_CALLS \\\n533\t         SMART_RENAME_OVERFLOW_SLOTS SMART_RENAME_FIRST_THRESHOLD \\\n534\t         SMART_RENAME_ONGOING_THRESHOLD SMART_RENAME_REATTACH_INTERVAL \\\n535\t         SMART_RENAME_CB_THRESHOLD SMART_RENAME_LOCK_STALE \\\n536\t         SMART_RENAME_LLM_TIMEOUT SMART_RENAME_LOG_LEVEL; do unset \"$v\" 2>/dev/null; done\n537\t\n538\techo \"-- defaults --\"\n539\tconfig_load\n540\tassert_eq \"enabled default\" \"true\" \"$(config_get enabled)\"\n541\tassert_eq \"model default\" \"claude-haiku-4-5\" \"$(config_get model)\"\n542\tassert_eq \"budget default\" \"6\" \"$(config_get max_budget_calls)\"\n543\tassert_eq \"first_threshold default\" \"20\" \"$(config_get first_call_work_threshold)\"\n544\tassert_eq \"lock_stale_seconds default\" \"60\" \"$(config_get lock_stale_seconds)\"\n545\t\n546\techo \"-- env overrides --\"\n547\texport SMART_RENAME_BUDGET_CALLS=10\n548\texport SMART_RENAME_FIRST_THRESHOLD=15\n549\tconfig_load\n550\tassert_eq \"env budget\" \"10\" \"$(config_get max_budget_calls)\"\n551\tassert_eq \"env first\" \"15\" \"$(config_get first_call_work_threshold)\"\n552\tunset SMART_RENAME_BUDGET_CALLS SMART_RENAME_FIRST_THRESHOLD\n553\t\n554\techo \"-- user config file overrides defaults --\"\n555\tcat > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/config.json\" <<EOF\n556\t{\"max