"\n754\t  log_dir=\"$base_dir/logs\"\n755\t  mkdir -p \"$log_dir\"\n756\t  log_file=\"$log_dir/$session_id.jsonl\"\n757\t  ts=\"$(date -u +\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\"\n758\t\n759\t  jq -nc \\\n760\t    --arg ts \"$ts\" --arg level \"$level\" --arg event \"$event\" \\\n761\t    --argjson data \"$data\" \\\n762\t    '{ts: $ts, level: $level, event: $event} + $data' \\\n763\t    >> \"$log_file\" 2>/dev/null || true\n764\t}\n765\t```\n766\t\n767\t- [ ] **Step 4: Run test + commit**\n768\t\n769\t```bash\n770\tbash tests/unit/test-logger.sh\n771\tgit add scripts/lib/logger.sh tests/unit/test-logger.sh\n772\tgit commit -m \"feat(v1.5): add lib/logger.sh (uses config_get; safe JSON via jq)\"\n773\t```\n774\t\n775\t---\n776\t\n777\t### Task 2.3: Refactor `tests/unit/test-state.sh` for config integration\n778\t\n779\tstate.sh already falls back to env when config.sh is absent. Now verify it uses `config_get` when config.sh IS sourced.\n780\t\n781\t**Files:**\n782\t- Modify: `tests/unit/test-state.sh`\n783\t\n784\t- [ ] **Step 1: Append integration test to `tests/unit/test-state.sh`**\n785\t\n786\tBefore the final `rm -rf \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA\"`, add:\n787\t\n788\t```bash\n789\techo \"-- config_get integration: lock_stale honored via config.json --\"\n790\t# Source config.sh and set a config-level override\n791\tsource \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../../scripts/lib/config.sh\"\n792\tunset SMART_RENAME_LOCK_STALE\n793\tcat > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/config.json\" <<EOF\n794\t{\"lock_stale_seconds\": 999}\n795\tEOF\n796\tconfig_load\n797\tstale=$(_state_lock_stale_seconds)\n798\tassert_eq \"config_get wins over default\" \"999\" \"$stale\"\n799\t```\n800\t\n801\t- [ ] **Step 2: Run test + commit**\n802\t\n803\t```bash\n804\tbash tests/unit/test-state.sh\n805\tgit add tests/unit/test-state.sh\n806\tgit commit -m \"test(v1.5): verify state.sh reads lock_stale from config.sh when sourced\"\n807\t```\n808\t\n809\t---\n810\t\n811\t## Phase 3: Transcript parser\n812\t\n813\t### Task 3.1: Create `lib/tra