CRIPT_PATH\"\n2448\t```\n2449\t\n2450\tIf the CLI exits non-zero, report the error message verbatim. Do not retry automatically.\n2451\t```\n2452\t\n2453\t- [ ] **Step 3: Manual smoke test**\n2454\t\n2455\tIn an interactive Claude Code session, exercise:\n2456\t```\n2457\t/smart-rename freeze\n2458\t/smart-rename explain\n2459\t/smart-rename unfreeze\n2460\t/smart-rename my-test-anchor\n2461\t/smart-rename explain\n2462\t/smart-rename unanchor\n2463\t```\n2464\t\n2465\tVerify each command produces expected output and state mutations.\n2466\t\n2467\t- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n2468\t\n2469\t```bash\n2470\tgit add scripts/smart-rename-cli.sh skills/smart-rename/SKILL.md\n2471\tgit commit -m \"feat(v1.5): complete skill (all 7 subcommands; suggest consumes budget)\"\n2472\t```\n2473\t\n2474\t---\n2475\t\n2476\t## Phase 8: Integration tests + v1 deletion\n2477\t\n2478\t### Task 8.1: Comprehensive integration tests\n2479\t\n2480\tAdds coverage for: T3 multi-Stop, T4 pivot, T5 force/overflow, T6 anchor persistence after native rename.\n2481\t\n2482\t**Files:**\n2483\t- Create: `tests/integration/test-end-to-end.sh`\n2484\t- Create: `tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-qa.jsonl`\n2485\t- Create: `tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-pivot.jsonl`\n2486\t\n2487\t- [ ] **Step 1: Create Q&A fixture**\n2488\t\n2489\t`tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-qa.jsonl`:\n2490\t```jsonl\n2491\t{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"What does useEffect cleanup do in React?\"}}\n2492\t{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The cleanup function in useEffect runs before the effect re-executes or when the component unmounts. It's used for clearing timers, canceling subscriptions, or removing event listeners.\"}]}}\n2493\t```\n2494\t\n2495\t- [ ] **Step 2: Create pivot fixture**\n2496\t\n2497\t`tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-pivot.jsonl`:\n2498\t```jsonl\n2499\t{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Fix the JWT auth bug\"}}\n2500\t{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Looking at JWT logic.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"1\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"src/auth/jwt.ts\"}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"2\",\"name\":\"Edit\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"src/auth/jwt.ts\",\"old_string\":\"x\",\"new_string\":\"y\"}}]}}\n2501\t{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Actually, let's switch — build a CI workflow for deploying to Vercel instead\"}}\n2502\t{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Switching gears.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"3\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\".github/workflows/vercel.yml\",\"content\":\"name: deploy\"}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"4\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"git add\"}}]}}\n2503\t```\n2504\t\n2505\t- [ ] **Step 3: Create `tests/integration/test-end-to-end.sh`**\n2506\t\n2507\t```bash\n2508\t#!/usr/bin/env bash\n2509\tset -euo pipefail\n2510\t\n2511\tSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\n2512\tREPO_DIR=\"$(cd \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../..\" && pwd)\"\n2513\tHOOK=\"$REPO_DIR/scripts/rename-hook.sh\"\n2514\t\n2515\tPASS=0; FAIL=0\n2516\tassert_eq() { local d=\"$1\" e=\"$2\" a=\"$3\"; [[ \"$e\" == \"$a\" ]] && { echo \"  ✓ $d\"; ((PASS++)) || true; } || { echo \"  ✗ $d: '$e' vs '$a'\"; ((FAIL++)) || true; }; }\n2517\t\n2518\texport CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA=\"$(mktemp -d)\"\n2519\texport PATH=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/../mocks:$PATH\"\n2520\t\n2521\trun_hook() {\n2522\t  local transcript=\"$1\" sid=\"$2\"\n2523\t  jq -nc --arg sid \"$sid\" --arg tp \"$transcript\" --arg cwd \"$PWD\" \\\n2524\t    '{session_id:$sid, transcript_path:$tp, cwd:$cwd}' | bash \"$HOOK\"\n2525\t}\n2526\t\n2527\techo \"=== end-to-end integration tests ===\"\n2528\t\n2529\techo \"-- Q&A: low score, no LLM call --\"\n2530\ttqa=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2531\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-qa.jsonl\" \"$tqa\"\n2532\trun_hook \"$tqa\" \"sess-qa\"\n2533\tassert_eq \"no LLM\" \"0\" \"$(jq -r '.calls_made // 0' \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-qa.json\")\"\n2534\t\n2535\techo \"-- Feature: threshold met → LLM call + title written (pre-seeded score to 20) --\"\n2536\tunset MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE\n2537\texport MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE='[{\"type\":\"result\",\"is_error\":false,\"duration_ms\":200,\"total_cost_usd\":0.05,\"structured_output\":{\"domain\":\"auth\",\"clauses\":[\"add rate limiting\"]}}]'\n2538\ttf=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2539\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tf\"\n2540\t# N3: pre-seed accumulated_score so the delta from this fixture (~13) pushes total past threshold 20.\n2541\t# This documents the intent explicitly rather than relying on coincidental fixture arithmetic.\n2542\tmkdir -p \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state\"\n2543\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", accumulated_score:10, title_struct:null, calls_made:0, overflow_used:0, failure_count:0, llm_disabled:false, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2544\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-feat.json\"\n2545\trun_hook \"$tf\" \"sess-feat\"\n2546\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-feat.json\")\n2547\tassert_eq \"calls_made 1\" \"1\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.calls_made')\"\n2548\tassert_eq \"title set\" \"auth: add rate limiting\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.rendered_title')\"\n2549\tassert_eq \"JSONL has custom-title\" \"custom-title\" \"$(tail -1 \"$tf\" | jq -r '.type')\"\n2550\tassert_eq \"last_processed_signature set\" \"true\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq 'has(\"last_processed_signature\")')\"\n2551\t\n2552\techo \"-- Writer failure: state NOT promoted, signature NOT advanced (R1) --\"\n2553\ttfw=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2554\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tfw\"\n2555\tchmod 444 \"$tfw\"   # readonly → writer_append_title returns non-zero\n2556\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", accumulated_score:15, title_struct:null, calls_made:0, overflow_used:0, failure_count:0, llm_disabled:false, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2557\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-wf.json\"\n2558\trun_hook \"$tfw\" \"sess-wf\"\n2559\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-wf.json\")\n2560\t# title_struct should remain null (not promoted), rendered_title empty\n2561\tassert_eq \"rendered_title empty (not promoted)\" \"\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.rendered_title // \"\"')\"\n2562\t# signature should be empty (not advanced)\n2563\tassert_eq \"signature not advanced\" \"\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.last_processed_signature // \"\"')\"\n2564\tchmod 644 \"$tfw\"\n2565\t\n2566\techo \"-- LLM failure increments failure_count --\"\n2567\texport MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE=fail\n2568\ttf2=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2569\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tf2\"\n2570\trun_hook \"$tf2\" \"sess-fail\"\n2571\tassert_eq \"failure 1\" \"1\" \"$(jq -r '.failure_count // 0' \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-fail.json\")\"\n2572\tunset MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE\n2573\t\n2574\techo \"-- Circuit breaker trips after 3 failures --\"\n2575\texport MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE=fail\n2576\ttcb=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2577\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tcb\"\n2578\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", failure_count:2, llm_disabled:false, calls_made:0, overflow_used:0, accumulated_score:100, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2579\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-cb.json\"\n2580\trun_hook \"$tcb\" \"sess-cb\"\n2581\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-cb.json\")\n2582\tassert_eq \"failure 3\" \"3\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.failure_count')\"\n2583\tassert_eq \"llm_disabled\" \"true\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.llm_disabled')\"\n2584\tunset MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE\n2585\t\n2586\techo \"-- Idempotency: same signature does NOT double-count (pre-seed so first call fires) --\"\n2587\tunset MOCK_CLAUDE_MODE\n2588\texport MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE='[{\"type\":\"result\",\"is_error\":false,\"duration_ms\":200,\"total_cost_usd\":0.05,\"structured_output\":{\"domain\":\"test\",\"clauses\":[\"a\"]}}]'\n2589\ttid=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2590\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tid\"\n2591\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", accumulated_score:15, title_struct:null, calls_made:0, overflow_used:0, failure_count:0, llm_disabled:false, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2592\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-idem.json\"\n2593\trun_hook \"$tid\" \"sess-idem\"\n2594\t# Second run with SAME file → same signature → scorer skips\n2595\trun_hook \"$tid\" \"sess-idem\"\n2596\tassert_eq \"calls_made still 1 after 2 hook runs on same file\" \"1\" \"$(jq -r '.calls_made' \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-idem.json\")\"\n2597\t\n2598\techo \"-- Multi-stop: file grows on second run → signature differs → proceeds --\"\n2599\ttms=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2600\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-multi-stop.jsonl\" \"$tms\"\n2601\t# Truncate to first assistant block to simulate mid-agentic-loop\n2602\thead -2 \"$tms\" > \"${tms}.part1\"\n2603\trun_hook \"${tms}.part1\" \"sess-ms\"\n2604\ts_part=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-ms.json\")\n2605\t# Now run with full file (size differs → signature differs → scorer proceeds)\n2606\trun_hook \"$tms\" \"sess-ms\"\n2607\ts_full=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-ms.json\")\n2608\t# active_files should have accumulated more files in the second run\n2609\tpart_files=$(echo \"$s_part\" | jq -r '.active_files_recent | length')\n2610\tfull_files=$(echo \"$s_full\" | jq -r '.active_files_recent | length')\n2611\t[[ \"$full_files\" -ge \"$part_files\" ]] && { echo \"  ✓ signature-based idempotency allowed mid-turn re-processing\"; ((PASS++)) || true; } || { echo \"  ✗ full=$full_files part=$part_files\"; ((FAIL++)) || true; }\n2612\t\n2613\techo \"-- Manual /rename sets title_override (not anchor) --\"\n2614\ttman=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2615\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tman\"\n2616\tjq -nc '{type:\"custom-title\", customTitle:\"My custom free-form title\"}' >> \"$tman\"\n2617\trun_hook \"$tman\" \"sess-man\"\n2618\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-man.json\")\n2619\tassert_eq \"title_override set\" \"My custom free-form title\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.manual_title_override')\"\n2620\tassert_eq \"rendered is override\" \"My custom free-form title\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.rendered_title')\"\n2621\t\n2622\techo \"-- Anchor persistence: /rename nativo then new hook → still honors override --\"\n2623\t# Run second hook on the same session: should NOT overwrite manual title with new LLM output\n2624\trun_hook \"$tman\" \"sess-man\"\n2625\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-man.json\")\n2626\tassert_eq \"override persists\" \"My custom free-form title\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.manual_title_override')\"\n2627\tassert_eq \"rendered still override\" \"My custom free-form title\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.rendered_title')\"\n2628\t\n2629\techo \"-- Pivot: domain changes are reflected when LLM returns new domain (pre-seeded state with existing title_struct) --\"\n2630\texport MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE='[{\"type\":\"result\",\"is_error\":false,\"duration_ms\":200,\"total_cost_usd\":0.05,\"structured_output\":{\"domain\":\"ci\",\"clauses\":[\"add vercel workflow\"]}}]'\n2631\t# Pre-seed: session already has a title (title_struct set) so ongoing_threshold=40 applies.\n2632\t# Fixture delta is ~5; we pre-seed accumulated_score=40 so decision is CALL.\n2633\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", accumulated_score:40, title_struct:{domain:\"auth\",clauses:[\"old\"]}, rendered_title:\"auth: old\", calls_made:1, overflow_used:0, failure_count:0, llm_disabled:false, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2634\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-pv.json\"\n2635\ttpv=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2636\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-pivot.jsonl\" \"$tpv\"\n2637\trun_hook \"$tpv\" \"sess-pv\"\n2638\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-pv.json\")\n2639\tassert_eq \"pivot domain\" \"ci\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.title_struct.domain')\"\n2640\t\n2641\techo \"-- Force path consumes overflow when budget already at max --\"\n2642\ttfc=$(mktemp).jsonl\n2643\tcp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/../fixtures/transcript-v15-feature.jsonl\" \"$tfc\"\n2644\tjq -nc '{version:\"1.5\", title_struct:{domain:\"x\",clauses:[\"a\"]}, rendered_title:\"x: a\", calls_made:6, overflow_used:0, force_next:true, accumulated_score:0, last_processed_signature:\"\"}' \\\n2645\t  > \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-force.json\"\n2646\trun_hook \"$tfc\" \"sess-force\"\n2647\ts=$(cat \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/state/sess-force.json\")\n2648\tassert_eq \"overflow incremented\" \"1\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.overflow_used')\"\n2649\tassert_eq \"force consumed\" \"false\" \"$(echo \"$s\" | jq -r '.force_next')\"\n2650\t\n2651\trm -rf \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA\"\n2652\techo \"\"\n2653\techo \"Result: $PASS passed, $FAIL failed\"\n2654\t[[ $FAIL -eq 0 ]]\n2655\t```\n2656\t\n2657\t- [ ] **Step 4: Run integration + full suite**\n2658\t\n2659\t```bash\n2660\tbash tests/integration/test-end-to-end.sh\n2661\tbash tests/run-tests.sh\n2662\t```\n2663\tExpected: all pass.\n2664\t\n2665\t- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n2666\t\n2667\t```bash\n2668\tgit add tests/integration/ tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-qa.jsonl tests/fixtures/transcript-v15-pivot.jsonl\n2669\tgit commit -m \"test(v1.5): integration tests incl. multi-stop, pivot, force/overflow, anchor persistence\"\n2670\t```\n2671\t\n2672\t---\n2673\t\n2674\t### Task 8.2: Delete v1 scripts (only after integration passes)\n2675\t\n2676\t**Files:**\n2677\t- Delete: `scripts/generate-name.sh`, `scripts/session-writer.sh`, `scripts/utils.sh`\n2678\t- Delete: `tests/test-generate-name.sh`, `tests/test-rename-hook.sh`, `tests/test-session-writer.sh`, `tests/test-utils.sh`\n2679\t\n2680\t- [ ] **Step 1: Confirm integration is green**\n2681\t\n2682\t```bash\n2683\tbash tests/run-tests.sh\n2684\t```\n2685\tMust exit 0.\n2686\t\n2687\t- [ ] **Step 2: Delete v1 files**\n2688\t\n2689\t```bash\n2690\tgit rm scripts/generate-name.sh scripts/session-writer.sh scripts/utils.sh\n2691\tgit rm tests/test-generate-name.sh tests/test-rename-hook.sh tests/test-session-writer.sh tests/test-utils.sh\n2692\t```\n2693\t\n2694\t- [ ] **Step 3: Run suite again**\n2695\t\n2696\t```bash\n2697\tbash tests/run-tests.sh\n2698\t```\n2699\tStill green.\n2700\t\n2701\t- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n2702\t\n2703\t```bash\n2704\tgit commit -m \"chore(v1.5): remove v1 scripts (superseded by modular lib/; integration green)\"\n2705\t```\n2706\t\n2707\t---\n2708\t\n2709\t## Phase 9: Level 3 manual scenarios (cost cap $10)\n2710\t\n2711\t### Task 9.1: Level 3 scenarios\n2712\t\n2713\t**Files:**\n2714\t- Create: `docs/test-results/2026-04-14-level3-scenarios.md`\n2715\t\n2716\t- [ ] **Step 1: Define budget cap**\n2717\t\n2718\tHard cap: **$10 USD total across all Level 3 scenarios combined**. If cumulative `cost_usd` (sum from logs) approaches $8, stop and assess.\n2719\t\n2720\t- [ ] **Step 2: Document scenarios to run**\n2721\t\n2722\tWrite into `docs/test-results/2026-04-14-level3-scenarios.md`:\n2723\t\n2724\t```markdown\n2725\t# Level 3 Manual Scenarios\n2726\t\n2727\tBudget: **$10 USD hard cap** across all scenarios. Sum costs from logs:\n2728\t```\n2729\tfor sid in <session-ids>; do\n2730\t  jq -s 'map(select(.event == \"llm_call_end\")) | map(.cost_usd) | add' \\\n2731\t    \"$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/logs/$sid.jsonl\"\n2732\tdone | awk '{s+=$1} END {printf \"Total so far: $%.4f\\n\", s}'\n2733\t```\n2734\tIf sum > $8, stop.\n2735\t\n2736\t## Scenario A: Short bugfix (~10 turns)\n2737\t- Fresh project; prompt: a small bug involving 1-2 files.\n2738\t- Expected: 1-2 LLM calls, title like `auth: fix X`.\n2739\t- Record: turn count, calls_made, total cost, subjective title quality.\n2740\t\n2741\t## Scenario B: Long feature (~30 turns)\n2742\t- Prompt a feature with 4-6 sub-tasks.\n2743\t- Expected: title evolves 3-5 times; budget hits 6 before session ends.\n2744\t- Record: title evolution history, budget exhaustion behavior.\n2745\t\n2746\t## Scenario C: Q&A exploration (~15 turns, no tool calls)\n2747\t- Conceptual questions only.\n2748\t- Expected: zero LLM calls (pre-filter skips).\n2749\t- Record: confirm `calls_made: 0`.\n2750\t```\n2751\t\n2752\t- [ ] **Step 3: Execute scenarios**\n2753\t\n2754\tHuman or agent runs them. Fill in the results file as they go. Stop if cost cap hit.\n2755\t\n2756\t- [ ] **Step 4: Commit results**\n2757\t\n2758\t```bash\n2759\tgit add docs/test-results/2026-04-14-level3-scenarios.md\n2760\tgit commit -m \"test(v1.5): Level 3 manual scenario results\"\n2761\t```\n2762\t\n2763\t---\n2764\t\n2765\t## Phase 10: Level 4 Computer Use (cost cap $10)\n2766\t\n2767\t### Task 10.1: Enable + execute Computer Use scenarios\n2768\t\n2769\t**Files:**\n2770\t- Create: `docs/test-results/2026-04-14-computer-use.md`\n2771\t\n2772\t- [ ] **Step 1: Enable Computer Use**\n2773\t\n2774\tIn interactive session: `/mcp` → find `computer-use` → Enable. Grant macOS Accessibility + Screen Recording permissions.\n2775\t\n2776\t- [ ] **Step 2: Define budget cap**\n2777\t\n2778\tHard cap: **$10 USD for all Computer Use scenarios**. Same monitoring as Level 3.\n2779\t\n2780\t- [ ] **Step 3: Execute scenarios**\n2781\t\n2782\tWrite into `docs/test-results/2026-04-14-computer-use.md` as you go:\n2783\t\n2784\t1. **Smoke test (~5 turns):** agent drives a separate terminal, invokes `/smart-rename freeze`, verifies state.\n2785\t\n2786\t2. **Evolution (~10 turns):** agent sends coding prompts; observes state across turns; screenshots session picker with title visible.\n2787\t\n2788\t3. **Controls chain:** `freeze` → 2 turns → `explain` → `unfreeze` → `force` → `<anchor>` → `explain`. Screenshot each step.\n2789\t\n2790\t4. **`/rename` nativo detection:** agent uses native `/rename`; verifies `manual_title_override` via state.\n2791\t\n2792\t5. **Circuit breaker (optional):** try to force 3 real LLM failures (e.g., unplug network briefly). If infeasible, skip.\n2793\t\n2794\tRecord calibration suggestions (e.g., \"first_call threshold of 20 feels too low for my patterns\").\n2795\t\n2796\t- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n2797\t\n2798\t```bash\n2799\tgit add docs/test-results/2026-04-14-computer-use.md\n2800\tgit commit -m \"test(v1.5): Level 4 Computer Use usability report\"\n2801\t```\n2802\t\n2803\t---\n2804\t\n2805\t## Phase 11: Documentation (after Level 3/4 calibration)\n2806\t\n2807\t### Task 11.1: Apply any threshold tuning discovered in Level 3/4\n2808\t\n2809\t**Files:**\n2810\t- Modify: `config/default-config.json` (only if Level 3/4 suggested changes)\n2811\t\n2812\t- [ ] **Step 1: Review Level 3/4 reports for calibration suggestions**\n2813\t\n2814\t- [ ] **Step 2: If changes needed, apply and commit**\n2815\t\n2816\t```bash\n2817\t# Example: adjust first_call_work_threshold from 20 to 30\n2818\tjq '.first_call_work_threshold = 30' config/default-config.json > config/default-config.json.tmp && mv config/default-config.json.tmp config/default-config.json\n2819\tgit add config/default-config.json\n2820\tgit commit -m \"tune(v1.5): adjust thresholds per Level 3/4 findings\"\n2821\t```\n2822\t\n2823\t### Task 11.2: Update README, CHANGELOG, plugin.json\n2824\t\n2825\t**Files:**\n2826\t- Modify: `.claude-plugin/plugin.json`\n2827\t- Modify: `README.md`\n2828\t- Modify: `CHANGELOG.md`\n2829\t\n2830\t- [ ] **Step 1: Bump plugin version**\n2831\t\n2832\t```bash\n2833\tjq '.version = \"1.5.0\"' .claude-plugin/plugin.json > .claude-plugin/plugin.json.tmp && mv .claude-plugin/plugin.json.tmp .claude-plugin/plugin.json\n2834\t```\n2835\t\n2836\t- [ ] **Step 2: Replace README.md with v1.5 version**\n2837\t\n2838\tSections to rewrite:\n2839\t1. **\"How it works\"**: paste the 8-step pipeline diagram from v1.5 spec §3.1.\n2840\t2. **\"Configuration\"**: table of env vars from v1.5 spec §10.3, each with default + one-line description.\n2841\t3. **NEW section \"Cost model\"** between \"How it works\" and \"Configuration\":\n2842\t   > Each LLM call in OAuth mode costs ~$0.10 because `claude -p` loads the full Claude Code context (~80k tokens of cache creation). The plugin budgets 6 calls per session (≈$0.60/session) with 2 manual overflow slots via `/smart-rename force`. Using `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` with `--bare` would reduce cost by ~250× but isn't the default (see v1.5 spec §1).\n2843\t4. **FAQ additions**:\n2844\t   - \"Why is there a budget?\" → cost model\n2845\t   - \"How does the plugin decide when to rename?\" → work-score\n2846\t   - \"What if I want to control the name myself?\" → `/smart-rename <name>` or `freeze`\n2847\t5. **REMOVE**: all `update_interval` references.\n2848\t6. **\"Subcommands\"**: list all 7 with one-line descriptions.\n2849\t7. **Quick Start**: include `/smart-rename explain` as verification.\n2850\t\n2851\t- [ ] **Step 3: Update CHANGELOG.md**\n2852\t\n2853\tPrepend:\n2854\t```markdown\n2855\t## 1.5.0 — <ISO date of release>\n2856\t\n2857\t### Changed (breaking)\n2858\t- Complete rewrite as modular bash (scripts/lib/*.sh).\n2859\t- Title format now `domain: clause1, clause2, ...` (was kebab-case).\n2860\t- Deterministic throttling via work_score replaces fixed 3-message interval.\n2861\t- Budget model: 6 LLM calls per session + 2 manual overflow slots.\n2862\t- State schema version 1.5 (v1 states — if any existed in practice — not migrated).\n2863\t\n2864\t### Added\n2865\t- Structured output via `claude -p --json-schema`.\n2866\t- Subcommands: `/smart-rename <name>`, `freeze`, `unfreeze`, `force`, `explain`, `unanchor`.\n2867\t- Detection of `/rename` nativo as `manual_title_override` (free-form, verbatim).\n2868\t- Distinction between `manual_anchor` (domain slug) and `manual_title_override` (full title).\n2869\t- Circuit breaker after 3 consecutive LLM failures.\n2870\t- JSONL structured logs per session (JSON-safe via `jq -nc --arg`).\n2871\t- Idempotency via `last_processed_signature` (turn_number:file_size) — covers agentic multi-stop.\n2872\t- Portable timeout (timeout/gtimeout/perl fall