ad, state_save, state_lock, state_unlock)\n   - 3 private helpers with `_` prefix (_state_file, _state_lockdir, _state_lock_stale_seconds)\n   - Single responsibility: state persistence + locking only\n   - No leaked business logic\n\n7. **Config Resolution**: `_state_lock_stale_seconds()` correctly:\n   - Checks if `config_get` is declared (forward-compatible with Phase 2)\n   - Falls back to `SMART_RENAME_LOCK_STALE` env var\n   - Defaults to 60 seconds (safe margin over 25s llm_timeout in config)\n\n8. **File Sizing**: 78 + 67 lines = 145 total. Appropriately scoped, no bloat.\n\n9. **Commit Message**: `feat(v1.5): add lib/state.sh with atomic save, portable lock, env fallback` — follows convention and accurately describes changes.\n\n10. **Test Hygiene**: Tests use `mktemp -d` for hermetic temp directories and clean up with `rm -rf` at the end. No side effects between runs.\n\n### Issues Found\n\n**None — Critical, Important, or Minor.**\n\nThe implementation is a perfect verbatim copy of the gate-reviewed plan. No deviations detected. All code quality concerns (atomicity, portability, error handling, interface design) are correctly addressed.\n\n### Assessment\n\n**PASS — Ready for integration.**\n\nThis module is production-ready and correctly implements the foundational state management layer required by all subsequent v1.5 modules. The 12-test suite provides confidence in both happy-path and failure-mode behavior across macOS and Linux platforms.\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/<user>/Documents/tech_projects/claude-code-smart-session-rename/scripts/lib/state.sh`\n- `/Users/<user>/Documents/tech_projects/claude-code-smart-session-rename/tests/unit/test-state.sh`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a37cf3f07e7b92286 (use SendMessage with to: 'a37cf3f07e7b92286' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 83287\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 118653</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"4d0c9335-b475-4759-a0c8-b69ad1aac6b4","timestamp":"2026-04-15T03:34:29.563Z","toolUseResult":{"status